article.headline: Princeton 61, Marshall 45
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Kyle Koncz scored 20 points to lead Princeton in its 61-45 win over Marshall on Saturday. Koncz, a junior forward, shot 5-for-10 from the field, including 4-for-8 from three-point range. Princeton (7-3) held the Thundering Herd to 39 percent shooting from the field, resulting in the lowest score of the season so far for Marshall (3-7). The Tigers were ahead seven at halftime. They then scored the first eight points of the second half to lead 35-20. Marshall cut Princeton's lead down to 10. But then Koncz hit a pair of foul shots after a technical foul was called against the Marshall bench. The Herd would get within 10 points of Princeton one more time after that. But they were never able to make it a single-digit margin. Senior guard Chris Ross led Marshall with 17 points, with 7-of-12 shooting from the field. Luke Owings hit nine points for Princeton, and Mark Dorris scored nine points for Marshall.
